{
  "texts": [
    "[53] employ HMM and Artificial Neural Networks (ANN) on the KPU corpus for three NE types.",
    "For HMM, unigrams, bigrams, and trigrams are used for training purposes, while word embeddings (word2vec) with window sizes (3 and 5) are used as contextual features for ANN.",
    "F-scores of 66.90% and 84.17% are achieved for HMM and ANN respectively.",
    "This study only uses one single type of word embeddings for text representation and only three types of NEs in the dataset.",
    "The experimentation also lacks performance comparison between other variants of ANNs or with existing state-of-the-art Urdu NER systems."
  ]
}